VALUES ('ec6bd28d-0bbf-425a-8ec1-207823c004ec', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Vincent van Gogh sold almost no paintings during his lifetime and was widely dismissed as an eccentric failure. His brother Theo, however, kept meticulous records and preserved hundreds of canvases that buyers had ignored. ______, the very works the public once rejected now hang in the world''s most celebrated museums.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"Today,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it marks the present-day reversal of the artist''s earlier obscurity."},{"id":"B","text":"In summary,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the sentence introduces a new time-based reversal, not a recap of prior points."},{"id":"C","text":"Because of this,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: the museums'' acclaim is not caused by the public''s earlier rejection."},{"id":"D","text":"Granted,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Granted'' concedes a point, but the sentence asserts a triumphant outcome."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Establish the contrast across time
The passage notes the works were ones {{yellow:buyers had ignored}} during his life.
Step 2 — Choose the relationship
The final sentence shifts to the present, where those works are celebrated, so a present-time transition fits.
Distractor analysis:
- B: ''In summary'' would recap, but the sentence adds a new contrasting development.
- C: ''Because of this'' implies causation from rejection, which does not hold.
- D: ''Granted'' concedes to an opposing view, not present here.', 'The final sentence jumps to the present-day reputation of the works.', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'medium', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
